The paper discusses the challenges faced by wireless network providers due to the explosive demand for wireless internet services and proposes a cost-efficiency-based data traffic management scheme from the user's perspective. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) category. Additionally, the paper discusses the economic efficiency of data consumption, which suggests that it could also belong to the Computational Economics and Finance (cs.CE) category. The paper also discusses the real-time data traffic management algorithm, which could suggest that it belongs to the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) or Information Theory (cs.IT) categories. Finally, the paper proposes an integrated data traffic management scheme, which could suggest that it belongs to the Signal and Image Processing (cs.SI) category.
